cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.LG 

The paper focuses on location prediction on Twitter, which involves natural language processing, social network analysis, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) due to the text analysis aspect. The paper also touches on social media and information retrieval, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively. Finally, machine learning is used extensively in the paper, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
